cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper discusses adversarial attacks on clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of the attack, which suggests that it could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The attack is designed to work without knowledge of the true metric, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses empirical results on datasets, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
